Mrs Decker has spoken out previously, saying that she remembered how uncertain she was about the impending disaster that she filmed a message on her mobile phone to her husband, telling him she loved him.

'I assumed I was safe and I heard the roar like a train, and I heard it behind me, and I knew it was coming,' she told ABC News.

'And it was so loud that I knew that I needed to do something different. I knew staying put wasn't going to work.'

